  "response": "In many Asian countries, clothing sizes can be smaller compared to U.S. sizes. If you wear an XS in the U.S., you might find that you need to go up a size or two when shopping for clothes in Asia. Typically, a U.S. XS might correspond to a Small or Medium in Asian sizes, but this can vary by brand and country. It's always a good idea to check the specific size charts provided by the manufacturer or retailer to ensure the best fit.",
